# .cursorignore — hard-block list (files Cursor must NOT read or index at all).
#
# This file intentionally hard-blocks NOTHING today.
#
# Why it's empty of rules:
#   - Build output (out/, target/, node_modules/) is already excluded from
#     indexing via .gitignore, so there's no need to repeat it here.
#   - out/ holds generated cross-language code (the Python/TypeScript bindings
#     described in the root CLAUDE.md). That code must stay AI-readable so the
#     AI can reason about cross-layer / IPC communication — so it is
#     deliberately NOT hard-blocked here.
#   - Pure index-noise (large lockfiles, generated docs site, etc.) belongs in
#     .cursorindexingignore instead: those stay readable on demand but are kept
#     out of the index.
#
# Add real hard-blocks below ONLY if such files ever exist in this repo —
# e.g. secrets, credentials, .env files with live keys. Anything listed here
# becomes completely invisible to Cursor and the AI.
